ription":"Using ChatOps interfaces for website auditing and performance tracking over time","content":"<h1 id=\"using-chatops-interfaces-for-website-auditing-and-performance-tracking-over-time\"><a href=\"#using-chatops-interfaces-for-website-auditing-and-performance-tracking-over-time\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Using ChatOps interfaces for website auditing and performance tracking over time</h1>\n<p>Every web developer wants to build a website that adheres to the almost mythical “best practices” so that it is light and performant.</p>\n<p>But how exactly are developers supposed to measure performance? And what is considered to be a best practice when it comes to developing for the web?</p>\n<p>To solve the problems outlined above, Google created Lighthouse, a toolset that audits a site of your choice for a number of key metrics that relate to five different categories:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Performance</li>\n<li>Accessibility</li>\n<li>Best Practices</li>\n<li>Search Engine Optimization</li>\n<li>Progressive Web App </li>\n</ul>\n<p>This allows developers working on a new site to quickly test how their website performs against each metric, and Google provides a detailed report with customized tips for how to improve the metrics of your particular site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 1372 1394' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-a0299a0146d4d934da73e4a73ba50b09'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-a0299a0146d4d934da73e4a73ba50b09)' width='1372' height='1394' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAABBCAYAAABhNaJ7AAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAAUIElEQVR4nNVbaZBc1XXun6m4UgVamOntrd0908tMz74vmhmNNJoZLaPRDhJCgCSEbAiEHxhIRcYYsENhg%2byALUBISAhJWJAUTioL5aQqULG